string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_DISPLAY_MODE
string.body: Windowed: Allows you to change the window size, and view other applications on the same screen.\nFull Screen: Aion will take up the whole screen, and other programs will not be displayed.\nWindow Full Screen: Runs Aion in full screen mode, but still allows you to view other programs while running the game.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_DISPLAY_RESOLUTION
string.body: Adjusts screen resolution.\n Only adjustable in Full Screen and Pseudo Full Screen modes. \nLowering the setting will improve game performance.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_DISPLAY_COLOR
string.body: Adjusts number of colours displayed.\nOnly available in Full Screen mode,\nand lowering the setting will improve game performance.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_DISPLAY_BRIGHTNESS
string.body: Adjusts the brightness of the screen.\nOnly adjustable in Full Screen mode.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_GRAPHIC_BG
string.body: Sets the level of detail in background objects.\nLowering the setting will improve game performance.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_GRAPHIC_WATER
string.body: Adjusts the reflective distance and quality of water surfaces.\nLowering the setting will improve game performance.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_GRAPHIC_SHADOW
string.body: Adjusts the quality of all characters' shadows.\nLowering the setting will improve game performance.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_GRAPHIC_TRR_RANGE
string.body: Sets the maximum visible range for topography.\nSetting it to be closer will improve game performance.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_GRAPHIC_OBJ_RANGE
string.body: Sets the maximum visible range for objects.\nSetting it to be closer will improve game performance.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_GRAPHIC_TEXTURE
string.body: Sets the level of detail in the textures.\nLowering the setting will improve game performance.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_GRAPHIC_SHADER
string.body: Sets the level of the character and background detail.\nLowering the setting will improve game performance.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_GRAPHIC_WHETHER
string.body: Toggles weather effects.\nDisable to improve game performance.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_SHOWFRAME
string.body: Shows the current FPS at the top of the screen.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_FIXEDFRAMEOPTION
string.body: Automatically adjusts graphics settings\nto maintain a certain FPS range.\nRecommended for lower performance machines.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_GRAPHIC_CHAR_OPT
string.body: This option automatically optimizes the level of detail shown on other PCs\nwhen it detects that the player is in a densely populated area and suffering from lag.\nTurning this on in densely populated areas will improve game performance.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_GRAPHIC_ANTIALIAS
string.body: Smooths the outlines of objects.\nIncreasing the setting means smoother graphics, but may decrease game performance.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_GRAPHIC_GLARE
string.body: Toggles a bloom lighting effect.\nDisable to improve game performance.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_GRAPHIC_GLOW
string.body: Toggles glow effects on characters and background objects.\nDisable to improve game performance.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_GRAPHIC_MODEL_SHADER_LOD
string.body: Reduces the level of detail shown on more distant characters.\nTurning this on will improve game performance.

Selects the graphics engine used to render the screen.
Choosing the High Quality engine offers improved quality over the default engine,
as well as more detailed display options.
For better game performance, select the default engine.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_GRAPHIC_OVERALL_QUALITY
string.body: Automatically detects the optimal graphics quality settings based on the system specifications of the computer.\nFor better game performance, select the Best Performance option.

string.body: Sets the texture detail level.\nFor better game performance, choose a lower setting.

string.body: Displays weather effects such as showers and sandstorms.\nDisable this effect to improve game performance.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_GRAPHIC_HIGH_GLARE
string.body: Softens the objects on the screen.\nDisable this effect to improve game performance.

string.name: STR_GLOBAL_OPTION_DIALOG_TOOLTIP_GRAPHIC_HIGH_BG_BUMP
string.body: Displays the background contours in greater detail.\nFor better game performance, choose a lower setting.

string.name: STR_FAMILIAR_COMPOSE_TAB_BUTOONTIP
string.body:
Minion Combination

1. If you successfully combine two or more minions at evolution level 4 (Class A, B, C), you will receive one random minion of a higher class. If the fusion fails, you receive a random minion at evolution level 4.
2. If you fuse two or more (Class S) minions regardless of their evolution level, you will receive a random (Class S) minion.
3. The more minions you fuse, the higher the chances of success. There's a certain probability that you will receive a minion at evolution level 2 to 4. (A Class S minion only increases the probability of receiving a minion at evolution level 2 to 4.)

string.name: STR_LOBBY_F2P_INFO

additional time will be credited to their tickets.
You can find further information on the official website. Thank you!

string.name: STR_FAMILIAR_DIALOG_GROWTH_BUTOONTIP
string.body:
Minion levelling and evolution

XP received from hunting or quests can be partially converted into Minion Growth Points. Alternatively, click on the growth button and use up to 10 minions in the material window to obtain growth points. If you use the special minions as the material, you gain twice as many points as for minions of the same level. If you click on the evolution button for a minion which has reached its maximum growth, you can increase its evolutionary level.

string.name: STR_DEVANIONSKILLENCHANT_REINFORCE_REGIST_TOOLTIP
string.body:
Register enchantment slot

1. Open the skill window (K) and drag the applied Daevanion skill. Unapplied skills can be registered by right-clicking.
2. You can only register legendary Daevanion skills or higher.
3. Click on the slot with the target to enchant to select the skill to be registered.

Register fusion slot

2. Click on an empty slot and select the Daevanion Skill Book you want to register.

string.name: STR_MSG_TRANSFORMATION_COMPOSE_USER_INFO
string.body: 1. You can fuse two or more transformations with the same level. 2. If four or more transformations are fused, you don't receive a transformation with a lower level. 3. The list shows up to 60 transformations. 4. Once started, you cannot cancel the fusion.

string.name: STR_TRANSFORMATION_COMPOSE_REPEAT_USER_INFO
string.body: 1. If you select 'Repeat fusion', a constant fusion process will be attempted. 2. The fusion is repeated as many times as you still have registered materials. 3. If the transformation window is closed, the repeated fusion will be cancelled, but any fusions in progress will continue. 4. A constant fusion process cannot be attempted for fusions starting from legendary.
